piercer 1 hand 25dam 40 delay 5ac 5 mr<br>
<br>
Is this a weapon that is worthy of wielding (for my secondary char).  As I play a druid mainly I dont know much about weapons.  It was my belief that speed was of a main concern with 1 hand weapons, but 25 damage seems alot.  My seconday is a SK and I have been using a 2 handed weapon (17/30).  So any info on delay vs damage in simple terms would be helpful in deciding whether to start training  piercing or keep with 2 handed.<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
Drillin Anklebiter<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/unillon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nillon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>GD RPers</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/28/00 2:25:20 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/soj/itsme.jpg height=82 width=108></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wurmslayer</span><hr size=1> Wurmslayer is way over rated.... for a sk i'd get a mace of the shadowed soul. <p>Nillon, level 55 Myrmidon, Brell Serilis</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ukaiyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaiyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/29/00 1:24:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wurmslayer</span><hr size=1> Yeah it sucks...real bad.  Want to sell it to me? *grin*<br>
<br>
Kaiyn Darious<br>
51st Season Warrior <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/udyninvifargent.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dynin Vifargent</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/29/00 3:55:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wurmslayer</span><hr size=1> way over rated is kinda exagerated<br>
unless you can get a really better weapon easily it's still a really good weapon.. slow though<br>
<br>
since you have a nathsar greatsword i would tell you to keep using it though because it's faster and 2H weapons have a better damage bonus ( even if it doesnt matter much if your twink is low level ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/udrillin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drillin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/31/00 9:09:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wurmslayer</span><hr size=1> So as I understand it 2 handed weapons get a damage bonus?<br>
<br>
so if I had a class that could dual wield, I may be better off using 1 handed weapons with low delay, but with my Shadowknight I should probaly stick with a 2 handed weapon due to damage bonus.<br>
<br>
I really do not know much about weapons, and what makes a good one so I really am curious about this.<br>
<br>
Thanks <br>
Drillin Anklebiter<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/udyninvifargent.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dynin Vifargent</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/31/00 11:35:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wurmslayer</span><hr size=1> well..<br>
actually 1H weapons have a damage bonus too<br>
not going into details but for example that's why you're not hiting for 1 but for a minimal damage that depends on your skill<br>
<br>
2H bonus is higher because when using a 1H weapon you can dual wield<br>
but paladins and SKs are getting really kick ass 1H weapons with awesome stats wich kinda make up for the lack of dual wielding..<br>
<br>
basically stats ( dmg/dly ratio ) is the first thing to consider and speed is the second<br>
a fast weapon with same ratio than a slow one will do a lot more damage<br>
<br>
hrmm actually look is the first thing to consider but i'm not supposed to say this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tembdaraangelknight>Tembdara AngelKnight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/1/00 5:57:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wurmslayer</span><hr size=1> I knopw right now at 50 I get a + to my Critical hit with my main hand weapon. If I Crit with my off hand weapon I get no Plus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/usylvarinfoxblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sylvarin Foxblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/2/00 10:47:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wurmslayer</span><hr size=1> And here I thought their ability to cast spells made up for not being able to dual wield. :P <p><a href="http://www.eqforge.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=3209">Sylvarin Foxblade</a><br>
53rd <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/broguesofbrell">Rogue of Brell</a><br>
<a href="http://silvershadows.n3.net">Silver Shadows</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uthoricofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thoric of Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/3/00 10:45:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wurmslayer</span><hr size=1> A thought on wurmslayer for all you high level rangers--I was grouped with Ganon last night, and he was using a wurmslayer in his prime hand, with a fairly quick weapon in his off. The slower speed of the weapon allowed me to keep critters taunted off him quite a bit, while the high damage meant he was still doing good damage. This weapon might make a good alternative for those of you who are finding yourselves aggroed and dead a lot. <br>
<br>
Thoric Frosthammer<br>
Silent Redemption <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uredspinebladeslinge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Redspine Bladeslinge</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/3/00 12:32:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wurmslayer</span><hr size=1> We just got 3 of these last night.  Haven't had a chance to fight with it yet though.  But due to delay will only use it when grouped with my wife who is a shaman.  This allows me to use my FBSS and her Speed buff to help reduce that dly some.  But I don't have any other real high dmg weapons yet so figure this will be very nice till I get one.  This 1hander is as good as any 2hs that I have (not taking into account the 2h bonus wars get), plus I'll still get to utilize duel wield for that occasional off hand swing.  <br>
<br>
Oh, not only that, but this thing looks freakin cool as hell.  If only I could put my trident in my off hand for those social occasions!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uredspinebladeslinge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Redspine Bladeslinge</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/4/00 11:40:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wurmslayer</span><hr size=1> I got to use my Wurmslayer last night. Yes it is SLOW. But with FBSS and Alachrity(sp?) I was very please with this weapon!!  With these speed buffs the dly on this weapon was such that it didn't bother me at all.  And seeing things like...peirce for 109dmg, peirce for 98dmg (double attack) slash for 35dmg, slash for 20dmg...rocked!!  I'm sure better weapons exist, but we were able to obtain this weapon with a group of 4!! 51Champion, 46Shadow Knight, 50Ranger (tracked and pulled) 50Shaman.  We fear kitted, slowed, dotted the wurms and took them out with nearly no effort.  <br>
<br>
On avg I was peircing around 60ish, with high hits around 110dmg.  I would put my speed with FBSS and Buff around 22-25ish??? (that is only a guess...so don't slam me).<br>
<br>
Oh, word of wisdom.  Our SK put his Wurmslayer in his Range Slot and promptly threw it at a MOB!! DOAH....I would't recommend doing this!! Troll Intelligence once again proves itself!!<br>
<br>
If you want to know how to get this weapon or need any info on the quest send me a tell, I'll be happy to assist where I can.<br>
<br>
Redspine <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tembdaraangelknight>Tembdara AngelKnight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/4/00 9:37:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wurmslayer</span><hr size=1> HE DID WHAT????:?????<br>
<br>
YEOUCH! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dantes>Dantes</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://forums.eqrealms.com/ubb/icons/icon10.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/9/00 1:00:09 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.valorblade.com/dantes.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wurmslayer</span><hr size=1> I've actually noticed I get attacked more with Wurmslayer than I did without it, it makes it easier to taunt.  Last night I landed a crippling blow for 247 with it.  I think it's highly underrated.  Reguardless of the fact it's got a slow delay, it's still got an awesome ratio. <p><img src="http://www.valorblade.com/dantes2.jpg" width="305" height="138"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/udyninvifargent.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dynin Vifargent</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/10/00 1:34:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wurmslayer</span><hr size=1> wurmslayer is now a 1 hand slash weapon instead of a 1 hand piercing <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uredspinebladeslinge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Redspine Bladeslinge</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/14/00 2:30:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: wurmslayer</span><hr size=1> Nice crippler Dantes!!  And with a 1handed weapon!  I have noticed the same thing concerning taunts, another bonus for us tankers.  Down side is it KILLS your sta bar.  I simply have my wife keep her sta rejuvinator up for when it drains to 0.  I still think having a 1hand weapon with a 2h weapon stats kicks ass.  And can still duel wield a kick ass weapon in the off hand.<br>
<br>
